      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Perplexity Pro worth $20/month?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, Perplexity Pro at $20/month is well worth it for researchers, students, journalists, and professionals who rely on accurate, cited information daily. Unlimited Pro searches let you use advanced AI models (GPT-4o, Claude) for every query. File uploads enable document analysis. The free tier with 5 Pro searches per day is generous, but heavy users will quickly justify the Pro subscription."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How accurate are Perplexity's citations?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Perplexity's citations are generally accurate and link directly to the source material. The system pulls from authoritative sources like academic papers, reputable news outlets, official documentation, and established websites. However, we recommend verifying critical citations, as no AI system is 100% perfect. In our testing, approximately 95% of citations correctly supported the claims they were attached to."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is Perplexity's Pro Search?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Pro Search is Perplexity's premium search mode that uses the most advanced AI models (GPT-4o, Claude 3.5, and Perplexity's own models) to provide deeper, more comprehensive answers. It performs multi-step reasoning, re-searches topics for more information when needed, and produces more detailed citations. Free users get 5 Pro Searches every 4 hours, while Pro subscribers get unlimited access."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Who should use Perplexity AI?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Perplexity AI is ideal for students, researchers, journalists, analysts, and professionals who need accurate, cited information quickly. It excels at research, fact-finding, data gathering, and competitive analysis. It is less suited for creative content generation or tasks requiring original writing — ChatGPT or Claude are better choices for those use cases."
